  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/pull/4813 we are adding the `--produce-block-v3` flag for using the v3 block production APIs in the VC. We are supporting the existing `builder_proposals: bool` config for backwards compatibility, by translating `builder_proposals: false` to `builder_boost_factor=0`.\r\n\r\nAs described by @eserilev here (https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/pull/4813#issuecomment-1877266739) it would be good to have some more expressive options in the VC like:\r\n\r\n- `prefer_builder_proposals: bool`: shorthand for `builder_boost_factor=u64::MAX`\r\n- `builder_boost_factor: u64`: support for other values configured on a per-validator basis\r\n\r\nI don't think we necessarily need `--local-always` as this is what I was forced to translate `builder_proposals: false` to. If we deprecate `builder_proposals` then the \"local always\"/\"prefer local\" naming may be clearer.\r\n",
